text: I've been reading and hearing more and more about PyPy.
As far as I know implementations of dynamic languages written in the languages itself aren't such a rare thing, or am I not getting something?
Some even people call PyPy "the future" [of python], or see some sort of deep potential in this implementation.
What exactly is the meaning of this?
